    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>123500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Λῦσις">Λῦσι<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></name> <persName type="attested" key="">
                            <name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἄριστις"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀρ</supplied>ίστιος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Lysis fils d'Aristis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Lysis son of Aristis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Lysis figlio di Aristis.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Although both names are frequently used in Cyrene, the lettering allows to suggest that this man might be the father of one Aristis son of Lysis, 
                   a contributor mentioned at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065210</ref>, ii.105.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
